717961f-a.title: Manhattan: Avenue C - 14th Street (East)
717961f-a.text:
Avenue C, north across East 14th Street. An empty lot
occupies the 14th to 15th Street frontage. On the block north
is a gas holder of the donsolidated Edison Co. The utilitarian
building above (16th to 17th Streets) is the N. Y. C. Motor
Transport Building. At this point this avenue terminates and
traffic flows into Exterior Street. Eventually the latter will
become a portion of the East River Drive.
October 23, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

717958f-a.title: Manhattan: Avenue C - 14th Street (East)
717958f-a.text:
Ave. C, north from East 14th Street, showing a gas holder of the
Consolidated Gas Co. across the fenced area at the western part of the
14th to 15th Street block. North of same appears the Repair Shops of the
City of New York.
June 1, 1937.
L. Sperr.
